                answer: { zh: "丰收 → 供给增加（供给曲线右移）→ 价格下降。农产品需求通常缺乏弹性（PED < 1，因为是必需品）→ 价格下降的百分比 > 数量增加的百分比 → 总收入下降（TR = P × Q）。例如: 价格从£10降到£6（-40%），数量从100增到120（+20%）→ 收入从£1000降到£720（-28%）。这就是为什么政府常对农业实施价格支持政策。", en: "Good harvest → supply increases (supply shifts right) → price falls. Agricultural products usually have inelastic demand (PED < 1, necessities) → % fall in price > % rise in quantity → total revenue falls (TR = P × Q). Example: Price falls £10 to £6 (-40%), quantity rises 100 to 120 (+20%) → revenue falls £1000 to £720 (-28%). This is why governments often implement agricultural price support policies." }
