                answer: { zh: "(a) 消费:信心崩溃 → 预防性储蓄增加 → 消费大幅下降。降息效果被信心效应抵消。实际:美国储蓄率从2%升至8%，消费下降。(b) 投资:信心崩溃 + 信贷冻结 → 即使利率低，企业也不愿投资(预期回报率暴跌)。实际:美国投资下降20%。(c) 降息效果有限原因: ①流动性陷阱(利率接近零，无法再降) ②信贷渠道受阻(银行不愿放贷) ③信心效应主导(悲观预期压倒低利率激励) ④资产负债表衰退(家庭和企业忙于去杠杆，不愿借贷消费/投资)。这就是为什么需要财政刺激。", en: "(a) Consumption: Confidence collapse → precautionary saving rises → consumption falls sharply. Interest rate cut effect offset by confidence effect. Reality: US savings rate rose 2% to 8%, consumption fell. (b) Investment: Confidence collapse + credit freeze → even with low rates, firms won't invest (expected returns plummeted). Reality: US investment fell 20%. (c) Limited effect reasons: ①Liquidity trap (rates near zero, can't cut further) ②Credit channel blocked (banks won't lend) ③Confidence effect dominates (pessimism overwhelms low rate incentive) ④Balance sheet recession (households/firms deleveraging, won't borrow to consume/invest). This is why fiscal stimulus was needed." }
