              "GENIE CASE STUDY - Extreme privation supports critical period for language and attachment",

              "DAY CARE RESEARCH - Quality matters more than quantity for child development outcomes",

              "NICHD STUDY - Family factors more important than hours in day care",

              "CULTURAL VARIATIONS IN ATTACHMENT - Universal attachment but different expressions across cultures",

              "ADOLESCENT PHYSICAL CHANGES - Puberty triggers growth sexual maturation and emotional changes",

              "IMAGINARY AUDIENCE - Adolescent belief that everyone is watching and judging them",

              "PERSONAL FABLE - Adolescent belief they are unique and nothing bad will happen",

              "PEER PRESSURE - Conformity to peer norms peaks during early adolescence",

